-- Deutsche Bank, Klepierre, Renault: European Equity Preview
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2011-12-22T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/deutsche-bank-klepierre-renault-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  fell 0.5 percent to 237.29. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  declined 0.5 percent to 2,296.21. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
retreated 0.8 percent to 2,244.35.  Deutsche Bank AG  (DBK GY): The German bank was sued by
Kingate Global Fund Ltd. in  New York  over claims it refused to
honor an agreement to buy bankruptcy claims on the estate of
convicted con man  Bernard Madoff . Deutsche Bank dropped 0.9
percent to 28.38 euros.  Klepierre SA (LI)  :  Europe ’s second-largest mall owner
said it bought a shopping mall adjoining E. Leclerc hypermarket
in Roques-sur-Garonne, France, for 96.6 million euros ($126
million). Klepierre declined 0.9 percent to 21.05 euros.  Renault SA (RNO)  : The French carmaker wants to become
the market leader for electric cars in Germany, aiming for a
share of 10 percent to 15 percent, Die Welt reported, citing an
interview with Germany head Achim Schaible. Renault lost 0.5
percent to 26.66 euros.  Societe Generale SA (GLE)  : France’s second-largest bank
said  Michel Peretie , chief executive officer of its corporate
and investment banking unit, is leaving after three years in the
post and will be succeeded by Didier Valet, the bank’s chief
financial officer. Societe Generale retreated 3.4 percent to
16.63 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
